title **Figure 2.** Topological Feature Extraction via Vietoris-Rips Filtration\n<i>From raw telemetry to Betti curve signatures</i>

|Raw Telemetry|
start
:Receive feature vectors
 **x** = [pkt_size, latency, entropy]
 for each node in network;

|Point Cloud|
:Embed features into
 metric space ℝ³;

:Compute pairwise distances
 d(xᵢ, xⱼ) for all node pairs;

|Filtration|
:Initialize ε = 0;

repeat
  :Construct simplicial complex
   **VR**ε = {σ | d(xᵢ,xⱼ) ≤ ε  ∀ xᵢ,xⱼ ∈ σ}
   
   ε=0.1: isolated points (0-simplices)
   ε=0.3: edges form (1-simplices)
   ε=0.5: triangles fill (2-simplices);
   
  :Record topological births & deaths
   • New connected component → β₀ birth
   • New loop appears → **β₁ birth** ⚠️
   • Loop fills in → β₁ death
   • Void forms → β₂ birth;
   
  :ε += Δε;
  
repeat while (ε < ε_max?) is (yes)
->no;

|Persistence|
:Generate Persistence Diagram
 Plot (birth, death) for each feature
 
 ● Near diagonal = noise (short-lived)
 ◉ Far from diagonal = **real structure**;

:Compute Betti Curves
 β₀(ε), β₁(ε), β₂(ε)
 = count of k-dim features alive at ε;

|Anomaly Signal|
if (β₁ persistently elevated?) then (yes)
  :⚠️ **ROUTING LOOP DETECTED**
   Consistent with HNDL
   data hoarding pattern;
  #FCE4EC:Flag for GNN classification;
else (no)
  :✅ Normal topology
   No cyclic anomalies;
endif

stop

@enduml


