skinparam roundCorner 8
skinparam shadowing false

title **Figure 3.** GCN Message Passing Architecture\n<i>Two-layer Graph Convolutional Network with spectral normalisation</i>

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor<<input>> #E3F2FD
  BorderColor<<input>> #1565C0
  BackgroundColor<<hidden>> #FFF3E0
  BorderColor<<hidden>> #E65100
  BackgroundColor<<output>> #FCE4EC
  BorderColor<<output>> #C62828
  BackgroundColor<<op>> #F5F5F5
  BorderColor<<op>> #616161
}

rectangle "**Input Layer**\nx ∈ ℝⁿˣ³" as IL <<input>> {
  card "pkt_size" as f1
  card "latency" as f2
  card "entropy" as f3
}

rectangle "**GCNConv Layer 1**" as L1 <<op>> {
  card "h⁽¹⁾ = σ(D̃⁻½ Ã D̃⁻½ X W⁽⁰⁾)" as conv1
  card "ReLU activation" as relu
  card "Dropout (p=0.5)" as drop
}

rectangle "**Hidden Representation**\nh ∈ ℝⁿˣ¹⁶" as HL <<hidden>> {
  card "16-dimensional\nnode embeddings\n(learned features)" as h16
}

rectangle "**GCNConv Layer 2**" as L2 <<op>> {
  card "h⁽²⁾ = D̃⁻½ Ã D̃⁻½ H W⁽¹⁾" as conv2
}

rectangle "**Output Layer**\nlogits ∈ ℝⁿˣ²" as OL <<output>> {
  card "P(benign)" as pb
  card "P(malicious)" as pm
}

rectangle "**Classification**" as CL <<output>> {
  card "Softmax → argmax\nThreshold: P > 0.65" as cls
}

IL --> L1 : "W⁽⁰⁾ ∈ ℝ³ˣ¹⁶\n(48 params)"
L1 --> HL
HL --> L2 : "W⁽¹⁾ ∈ ℝ¹⁶ˣ²\n(32 params)"
L2 --> OL
OL --> CL

note right of L1
  **Message Passing Rule:**
  Each node aggregates features from
  its graph neighbours, weighted by
  the symmetric normalised adjacency:
  
  Ã = A + I  (self-loops)
  D̃ᵢᵢ = Σⱼ Ãᵢⱼ  (degree matrix)
  
  This is the Kipf & Welling (2017)
  spectral convolution formulation.
end note

note right of CL
  **Total Parameters: 338**
  (Intentionally lightweight for
  sub-80ms inference on CPU)
end note

@enduml


